Now that's a hard act to follow!<br><br>
Cookie and MTF zeroed in on some very important issues. <br><br>
About the most important things of impact for me that have come out of the Vietnam War is getting screwed up real bad, recognizing it, getting help, and really getting a second chance at life. Now how many people do you know who have a second chance to really make their life and the lives around them better? I have learned to see the view looking up from the bottom of the barrel, where I was and didn't know it, and I don't like it one bit. I have PTSD, but that's OK, because I know know what I don't have, too, and that is better than most people can say for themselves!<br><br>
It seems that I am travelling in a circle, because I am now closer to what it was that drove me away in the first place. Having BOC makes all the difference in the world. It is easier to face the blackness with friends you love who have been there too. If it were not for 'Nam, I would never have met the finest BOC here.  <br><br>
